{
  "texts": [
    "We randomly sample 20 topics from our dataset and evaluate the articles generated by our method and oRAG, the best baseline according to the automatic evaluation.Each pair of articles is assigned to 2 editors.",
    "We request editors to judge each article from the same five aspects defined in §4.2, but using a 1 to 7 scale for more fine-grained evaluation.",
    "While our automatic evaluation uses citation quality as a proxy to evaluate Verifiability, we stick to the Wikipedia standard of \"verifiable with no original research\" in human evaluation.",
    "Besides rating the articles, editors are asked to provide open-ended feedback and pairwise preference.",
    "After the evaluation finishes, they are further requested to compare an article produced by our method, which they have just reviewed, with its human-written counterpart, and report their perceived usefulness of STORM using a 1-5 Likert scale."
  ]
}